"{\"uid\": \"bucksfreepress.co.uk-news-24413915.olympics-2024-dutch-volleyballer-raped-milton-keynes-girl-12\", \"text\": \"CourtCrimeMilton Keynes  A Dutch man who travelled to the UK to rape a 12-year-old girl in Milton Keynes is set to represent his country at the Paris Olympics.  Steven van de Velde, a 29-year-old from The Hague, was jailed in 2016 after admitting to three counts of rape.  He had contacted a British schoolgirl\\u00a0via social media\\u00a0in 2014, and travelled to the UK to meet her several months later - despite being fully aware that she was just 12.  After giving her alcohol,\\u00a0Van de Velde raped her multiple times.  Sentencing Van de Welde atAylesburyCrown Court in\\u00a02016, the judge remarked that he was a talented beach volleyball player.  He told the defendant that his rape conviction meant he would never be able to realise his dream of representing the Netherlands in his sport.  Although the British judge jailed him for four years, Van de Welde was able to serve his sentence in the Netherlands, where he spent just one year in prison.  Media reports suggest that he\\u00a0has now qualified for the Paris Olympics - and that he and another volleyballer\\u00a0will travel to France next month for the event.  This website and associated newspapers adhere to the Independent Press Standards Organisation's     Editors' Code of Practice. If you have a complaint about the editorial content which relates to     inaccuracy or intrusion, then pleasecontact the editor here.     If you are dissatisfied with the response provided you cancontact IPSO here  \\u00a9 2001-2025. The Bucks Free Pressis owned and operated by Newsquest Media Group Ltd, an audited local newspaper network.  Visitnewsquest.co.ukto view ourpoliciesandterms.  The Echo Building, 18 Albert Road, Bournemouth, England BH1 1BZ. Registered in England & Wales | 01676637  Data returned from the Piano 'meterActive/meterExpired' callbackevent.  As a subscriber, you are shown80% lessdispla